%a{ :name => "rvm-use-default" }
%h3
  Use the user set default  ruby
%pre.code
  :preserve
    ∴  rvm use default
%a{ :name => "rvm-use-system" }
%h3
  Use the system ruby (as if no rvm)
%pre.code
  :preserve
    ∴  rvm use system
%a{ :name => "rvm-reset" }
%h3
  Reset to pre-rvm state.
%pre.code
  :preserve
    ∴  rvm reset
%h3
  Uninstall rvm installed 1.8.7 version
%pre.code
  :preserve
    ∴  rvm uninstall 1.8.7
%a{ :name => "rvm-gemdup" }
%a{ :name => "rvm-gemdup-default" }
%h3
  Install gems from ~/.gem/ruby/1.8/
%pre.code
  :preserve
    ∴  rvm gemdup default
%p
  note: gemset dump/load is much preferred over this.
%a{ :name => "rvm-gemdup-system" }
%h3
  Install gems from system gem dir (osx: /Library/Ruby/Gems/1.8) using current ruby
%pre.code
  :preserve
    ∴  rvm gemdup system
%p
  note: gemset dump/load is much preferred over this.

